*Set the Version
*Import the Data From the TSV File Downloaded from Qualtrics, Which Was Used to Conduct the Survey in Argentina.
*Relabel Unique Identifier
*Create Birthdate Variable Using %TD Format
*Create Birthdate Variable Using DD/MM/YYYY Format
*Create Election Date Variable in %TD Format

varlist.value: "date of October 22, 2017 election, in days, since 01jan1960"

value: *Create Days from Birth to Election Variable
*Create Days from Age 18 on Election Day Variable

//*According to https://www.timeanddate.com/date/duration.html, there were 6575 days between October 22, 1999  and October 22, 2017. Thus, those who turned 18 on election day were 6575 days old. Verfieid at: http://www.thecalculatorsite.com/misc/days-between-dates.php.
*Create Age Cutoff for Compulsory Voting Variable
//*exclude respondents older than 19 on election day.
//*exclude respondents younger than 16 on election day.

varlist.value: "respondent was 18 or 19 years old on election day, as defined by reported birth date"

value: *Create Indicator for Number of Items Selected in Vote Buying List Experiment
//*There are two control groups by design. This is a simple way to inflate the number of individuals assigned to the control within Qualtrics.

varlist.value: "number of items selected in vote buying list experiment"

value: *Create Indicators for the Control and Three Treatment Groups

varlist.value: "respondent was in control group for list experiment"
"respondent was in turnout buying group for list experiment"
"respondent was in positive vote buying group for list experiment"
"respondent was in negative vote buying group for list experiment"

value: *Create Indicator or Valid, Blank, or Null (Spoiled) Voting

varlist.value: "1 if voted for candidate OR cast blank or null/spoiled ballot; 0 otherwise"
